message.content: We see that if we apply function $f$ to a number, it results in the corresponding $x$-coordinate on the graph of $f$.  Notice that if we start with 3, we apply $f$ to get the value 6.  We then apply $f$ again to get 5.  Continuing this process, we have $3\to 6\to 5\to 3\to 6\to \dotsb$.  We see that $f$ applied three times will result in the original number, so $f$ applied ten times will result in $\boxed{3}$.
